<typeStatus id="548F06B26516FFF9FE80FE25FE04FE4B" box="[303,458,404,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="258">paralectotype</typeStatus>
) as in male, except face slightly narrower than frons; outer vertical seta smaller than inner vertical and ocellar setae. Abdomen lost, described as “ 
<emphasis id="B94064026516FFF9FCF9FE09FA41FE29" box="[854,1423,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="258">terebra basi inflata lamellis terminalibus angustis</emphasis>
” [terminalia with segment 8 wider basally].
</paragraph>
